AB  - In recent years, the increasing prevalence of mental health issues among higher education students has posed significant challenges for higher education institutions in managing these concerns. To address these challenges, artificial intelligence (AI) has been utilized in this field. To comprehensively understand the application of AI in mental health management for higher education students, we conducted a systematic review using the Preferred Reporting Items for Systematic Reviews and Meta-Analyses (PRISMA) methodology. The results indicate that the applications of AI in mental health management for higher education students primarily focus on four areas: mental health assessment, education, prediction, and intervention. These areas have exhibited significant effectiveness, leading to notable improvements in providing more objective, efficient, and accurate assessment and prediction results. Furthermore, they have contributed to enhancing the mental health education environment and strategies, thereby improving educational efficiency and offering personalized services. Additionally, they have augmented overall effectiveness and enabled more timely, cost-effective, and accessible interventions. In conclusion, the application of AI has demonstrated considerable potential in addressing the various challenges associated with mental health management for students in higher education. © 2025 The Authors.
