AB  - Social media use is common in adolescents and carries with it particular advantages and disadvantages, which may not be immediately apparent. Social media, first and foremost, is a platform for communication, social connection, and self-expression. It can be a way for adolescents to explore their identity and is an important means of education. The negative aspects of social media are numerous and include cyberbullying, sexting, exposure to triggering content, and encouragement of high-risk behaviors. The topic of social comparison is central to understand when discussing the influence of social media on adolescents. Furthermore, issues of privacy on the internet are incredibly important. For clinicians, social media provides opportunities for mental health education and therapeutic intervention with adolescents. This chapter provides an explanation and review of these platforms. Recommendations for clinicians on how to identify risks and encourage positive use of social media among adolescents are included. © The Editor(s) (if applicable) and The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2023.
